The code statements that lead to the bug are:
```java
// No restrictions on file writing operations
```
Reason:
The absence of any checks or restrictions on file writing operations allowed files to be written outside the designated starting directory, creating a security risk by enabling unauthorized access to higher-level directories.

The code statements that fix the bug are:
```java
protected boolean jailStartingDirectory = true;
public void setJailStartingDirectory(boolean jailStartingDirectory) {
    this.jailStartingDirectory = jailStartingDirectory;
}
```
Reason:
The introduction of the `jailStartingDirectory` variable, which is set to `true` by default, restricts file writing to the starting directory and its subdirectories. The setter method allows for this restriction to be toggled, enhancing security by preventing writes to unauthorized directories.

